<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#123#000020#       159#">Va. Code Ann. § 20-159</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_20-159"/><heading><desig>§ 20-159.</desig><title>Surrogacy contracts permissible</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> A surrogate, her husband, if any, and prospective intended parents may enter into a written agreement whereby the surrogate may relinquish all her rights and duties as parent of a child conceived through assisted conception, and the intended parents may become the parents of the child as provided in subsection D or E of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 20-158"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 20 -158">§ 20-158<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000020#       158#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Surrogacy contracts shall be approved by the court as provided in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 20-160"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 20 -160">§ 20-160<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000020#       160#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.  However, any surrogacy contract that has not been approved by the court shall be governed by the provisions of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 20-156"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 20 -156">§§ 20-156<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000020#       156#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> through <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 20-159"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 20 -159">20-159<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000020#       159#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> and <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 20-162"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 20 -162">§§ 20-162<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000020#       162#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> through <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 20-165"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 20 -165">20-165<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000020#       165#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> including the provisions for reformation in conformance with this chapter as provided in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 20-162"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 20 -162">§ 20-162<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000020#       162#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="1991 VA CH 600"><content><span normalizedCite="1991 Va. Ch. 600">1991, c. 600<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1991#000600#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier id